title.rendered: IND vs SA Tickets 2022, T20 Squad, Schedule, Venues, And Live Streaming Details

content.rendered:
From June 9, the Indian national team will take on the South African team planning to make up the difference ahead of the T20 World Cup starting in October. Indian team will be there as host and South Africa team will come to India. The match will be held at Arun Jaitley Stadium in Delhi. Both the teams have already arrived at the venue and will have to undergo the mandatory RTPCR testing before the match begins.

According to Delhi & District Cricket association (DDCA), there will be no bio bubble requirement this time, but there will be a regular RT-PCR testing.

So, let’s understand all about the match such as the both team’s squad, their live streaming and telecast and so on. Have a look,

Ind Vs SA T20 Squad

India

Deepak Hooda, Ruturaj Gaikwad, KL Rahul (Captain), Shreyas Iyer, Hardik Pandya, Axar Patel, Venkatesh Iyer, Ishan Kishan, Dinesh Karthik, Rishabh Pant (VC), Arshdeep Singh, Bhuveneshwar Kumar, Kuldeep Yadav, Harshal Patel, Yuzvendra Chahal, Umran Malik.

South Africa

Team Bavuma, Reeza Hendricks, Quinton De Kock, Heinrich Klaasen, Aiden Markram, Keshav Maharaj, Lungi Ngidi, David Miller, Anrich Nortje, Dwaine Pretorius, Wayne Parnell, Kagiso Rabada, Tristan Stubbs, Tabraiz Shamsi, Marco Jansen, Rassie van der Dussen,

Ind Vs SA T20 schedule & Venue

  • Ind Vs SA 1st Test – June 9th – Delhi
  • Ind Vs SA 2nd test – June 12th – Cuttack
  • Ind Vs SA 3rd Test – June 14th – Vishakhapatnam
  • Ind Vs SA 4th test – June 17th – Rajkot
  • Ind Vs SA 5th test – June 19th – Bengaluru

Ind Vs SA Live telecast and streaming details

India – In Indian the live telecast will be taken care by Star Sports Network which is the official broadcaster of IPL 2022 in India whereas the live streaming can be seen on Disney + Hotstar app.

For viewers are looking to watch these matches through live telecast only then then they can watch it on Star sports 3, Star Gold 2, Star Sports 1.

  • Saharan African continent – SuperSports Cricket
  • United Kingdom – Sky Sports
  • West Indies (Caribbean) – Live Telecast on Flow Sports and live streaming on Flow Sports app
  • United States and the neighbouring country Canada – Williow TV & ATN Cricket Plus
  • In New Zealand – Sky Sports
  • Australia – Fox Sports
  • Pakistan – Ten Sports Pakistan
  • Bangladesh – Gazi TV
